Interface AssertThatObject<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the object type.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AssertThatCastableObject<T>, AssertThatIterable<T>, AssertThatString

    public interface AssertThatObject<T>
    DSL for assertion on object.

    This interface is returned by the various methods assertThat exposed by TestSuite.

    Author:
    borettim

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean is(Matcher<? super T> matching)
      Check that the object is matching the passed matcher.

      default boolean isA(Class<? super T> clazz)
      Check that the object is of a specific class (or subclasses).
      default boolean isNot(Matcher<T> matching)

      default boolean isNot(T compareTo)

      default boolean isNotNull()
      Check that the object is not null.
      default boolean isNull()
      Check that the object is null.

    • Method Detail

      • is

        boolean is(Matcher<? super T> matching)
        Check that the object is matching the passed matcher.


        By default, assertion can only be used from the main thread of the test ; When used from another thread, the assertion will be lost. In the case the fastFail attribute of @Test annotation is used, the assertion may not be lost, in case the thread use an assertion method from the test object instance.

        Parameters:
        matching - the matcher.
        Returns:
        true if the assertion is valid ; If the assertion is false, depending on Test.fastFail() : If true, then fail the test, else, return false and the test will be failed later.
        See Also:
        The documentation of the fastFail attribute of the @Test annotation, regarding the action done by this assertion.
